        "id": 1017720
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-07-07T06:45:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This wraps each argument value using the func\u0027s own runtime (ctx.runtime(), created by the runtime.New() above), but opCtx belongs to the runtime that is actually evaluating the CUE — a different one. It works today because the label table in internal/core/runtime/index.go is a process-global, so cross-runtime label lookups during Decode happen to resolve; but any per-runtime state consulted during decoding would silently be wrong. Wrapping the arg with the calling opCtx\u0027s runtime would be more obviously correct.",
      "revId": "33f6c190c4175be335aeb12ac77332e210cbc795",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
